parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or lock up, leading to loss of control of the vehicle, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes hard to turn
the steering wheel pulls to one side
the steering wheel jerks or shakes
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the power steering indicator light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS control module can cause the anti-lock braking system to malfunction, leading to increased stopping distances and potentially causing accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Illuminated dashboard lights
including ABS
brake
traction control
and tire pressure monitoring system lights; intermittent warning signals; faulty soldering inside the module; connections break easily.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter motor can cause the vehicle to be unable to start, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing safety issues.
symptoms: Grinding or whirring sound when trying to start the vehicle; vehicle won't start; multiple attempts required to start the vehicle; clicking or grinding noise when starting the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the VSA modulator can cause the traction control system to malfunction, leading to increased risk of accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Illuminated dashboard lights
including traction control
ABS
and tire pressure monitoring system lights; faulty internal failure; inability to find replacement parts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various systems to malfunction, leading to safety issues and inconvenience.
symptoms: Smoke in the vehicle; electrical problem between the radio dash and middle car components; burning and melting of components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock actuator can cause the doors to be unable to lock or unlock, potentially causing safety issues.
symptoms: Doors unable to lock or unlock; no warning lamps.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the FCW system can cause the forward collision warning system to malfunction, leading to increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: "Failed FCW System" message on the dashboard; random beeping; unreliable system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the infotainment system can cause inconvenience and distraction while driving.
symptoms: Intermittent failure of the system; inability to use radio
Bluetooth
and cameras.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter can cause the vehicle to not start, leaving the driver stranded, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle does not start
the starter motor makes a clicking sound but the engine does not turn over
the starter motor grinds or makes a loud noise when attempting to start the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can cause engine damage, leading to premature engine failure, and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The oil level drops rapidly
the oil light comes on
the engine makes a knocking or grinding noise
black soot is visible at the tailpipe.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or injuries, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving
the vehicle loses power
the check engine light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the relay box can cause the vehicle to not start, leaving the driver stranded, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle does not start
the starter motor makes a clicking sound but the engine does not turn over.
